using Plots
using Distributions
using LinearAlgebra
In [2]:
# parameters that can be changed
REP = 1000000 # million iterations
N = 200 # larger dimension
n = 100 # smaller dimension
Out[2]:
100
In [3]:
# Experiment 1: Uniform from -sqrt{3} to sqrt{3} (to make mean 0 and variance 1)
ls = []
for i in 1:REP
    M = rand(Uniform(-sqrt(3),sqrt(3)), N, n) # random N*n matrix
    push!(ls, svdvals(M)[n]) # add smallest eigenvalue of M to ls
end

# Experiment 2: Random \pm 1 matrix
ls = []
for i in 1:REP
    M = rand(Uniform(-1, 1), N, n) # random N*n matrix
    M = map(sign, M) # random \pm 1 entries
    push!(ls, svdvals(M)[n]) # add smallest eigenvalue of M to ls
end

# Experiment 5: T-distribution w. 3 degrees of freedom
ls = []
for i in 1:REP
    M = rand(LocationScale(0, 1, TDist(3))*sqrt(1/3), N, n) # random N*n matrix
    push!(ls, svdvals(M)[n]) # add smallest eigenvalue of M to ls
end

ls = []

    M = rand(Poisson(1)-1, N, n) # random N*n matrix
    push!(ls, svdvals(M)[n]) # add smallest eigenvalue of M to ls

# Experiment 7: some weird asymmetric 2nd moment distribution
# basically distribution with PDF proportional to 1/x^4, and then shifting/scaling
f = x -> (x^(-1/3)-1.5)/sqrt(0.75)
ls = []
for i in 1:REP
    M = rand(Uniform(0, 1), N, n)
    M = map(f, M) # random N*n matrix
    push!(ls, svdvals(M)[n]) # add smallest eigenvalue of M to ls
end
